name: Tony Todd
summary: Prolific actor Tony Todd, renowned for his chilling portrayal of Candyman in the eponymous horror franchise, has passed away at the age of 69. Todd's haunting performance as the titular hook-wielding monster cemented him as a horror icon. Beyond the Candyman films, Todd's extensive filmography boasts memorable roles in the "Final Destination" series and the acclaimed war drama "Platoon." With hundreds of credits to his name, Todd's impact on the entertainment industry is immeasurable. His legacy as a master of the macabre and a versatile performer will forever be etched in the annals of film and television.

name: Heretic
summary: Heretic, a 2024 horror thriller, has garnered significant buzz with its unorthodox premise, which is seen as a potential game-changer for the year's cinematic offerings. Hugh Grant's portrayal of a sinister character has been highly praised, breaking away from his traditional charming roles. The film's ending has sparked polarized reactions and has been deemed "fascinating" and "polarizing." Critical reviews commend its mix of intellectual discourse, graphic violence, and Grant's transformed performance. However, the ending has been criticized for requiring further exploration and interpretation. Despite its divisive reception, Heretic has had a strong box office debut, raking in $1.2 million in previews, solidifying its position as a notable film in 2024.

name: Daniel Lurie
summary: Democrat Daniel Lurie, heir to the Levi Strauss fortune, has been elected as the new mayor of San Francisco, defeating incumbent London Breed. Lurie campaigned as an outsider and political neophyte, while Breed was seeking a second term. The victory is seen as a significant upset, with Lurie overcoming Breed's strong name recognition and endorsements from the Democratic establishment. Lurie's policy positions include addressing homelessness, crime, and housing affordability. His election has been met with mixed reactions, with some observers expressing optimism for change while others voice concerns about his lack of experience.

name: Bronny James
summary: The Los Angeles Lakers have assigned 19-year-old rookie Bronny James to the NBA G League team, South Bay Lakers. This move is part of the Lakers' plan to develop James and provide him with more playing time. The decision was made after James struggled to get minutes on the court for the Lakers. Despite being a highly touted prospect, James has yet to find his footing in the NBA, averaging only 1.2 points per game in limited appearances. The G League assignment will give him the opportunity to play a more significant role and gain valuable experience. The move has sparked mixed reactions, with some fans expressing disappointment that James will not be playing in the NBA and others supporting the opportunity for his growth. The New York Times reports that this move is part of a larger strategy by the Lakers to develop young talent and build a winning team.

summary: Duke University's men's basketball team will kick off their season against the University of Maine on Monday. The Blue Devils are led by freshman star Dariq Whitehead, who is expected to make a significant impact this season. However, Whitehead has been dealing with some off-court issues, including a recent DUI arrest. Duke has also added another five-star recruit to its 2025 class, AJ Swinton. The Blue Devils will be looking to build on their success from last season, when they reached the Final Four. Maine, on the other hand, is coming off a 10-21 season. name: Parole in place
summary: Several news articles report on the outcome of a court case regarding a Biden administration immigration program. The program, known as "Parole in Place," aimed to protect undocumented spouses and stepchildren of U.S. citizens from deportation. However, a federal judge has struck down the program, leaving the fate of affected families uncertain. The decision sparked concerns among immigrant advocates and families who benefited from the program. The ruling is a setback for the Biden administration's immigration policies, which have faced legal challenges and ongoing debates about immigration reform.

name: Aldi cheese recall
summary: Multiple news outlets, including TODAY, USA TODAY, CBS News, ABC7 Chicago, NJ.com, Taste of Home, Health.com, WCAX, New York Post, and AL.com, have reported a widespread recall of Brie cheese sold at Aldi and other stores due to potential Listeria contamination. The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has issued a warning to consumers to discard or return the affected products immediately. Listeria can cause serious infections, especially in pregnant women, those with weakened immune systems, and older adults. Affected brands include Saint Albray, Bijou, and Brie Rouzaire, and consumers are urged to check the packaging of their cheese for specific product details.

name: Nosferatu
summary: Early reviews of Robert Eggers' highly anticipated "Nosferatu" remake have emerged, hailing it as a chilling masterpiece. The film, inspired by the classic 1922 silent movie, has been praised for its faithfulness to the original while injecting a new level of horror. Eggers reportedly shares the chilling true tales that inspired his adaptation, while critics rave about the "devilish" and "seductively macabre" performances. The film's depiction of Count Orlok, played by Lily-Rose Depp, has been singled out as groundbreaking for Dracula stories, with reactions calling it a "magnum opus" that deserves awards consideration. The film's live musical score, side-part hairpiece, and the challenges of working with rats have also been topics of discussion. Overall, the first reactions to "Nosferatu" suggest a haunting and unforgettable cinematic experience.

summary: A major winter storm has brought heavy snowfall to Colorado and New Mexico, with some areas receiving up to three feet of snow. The storm is expected to continue through Saturday, with additional snowfall of up to 10 inches possible in Denver. The storm has caused power outages, road closures, and flight cancellations. In Colorado, the snow has buried homes and cars, and made travel treacherous. The storm is also bringing strong winds and cold temperatures, creating dangerous conditions for those who need to be outdoors. Warmer temperatures are expected to move into the region later in the week, but the snow and cold will likely linger for several days.

name: Rashida Jones
summary: Rashida Jones, daughter of the late legendary music producer Quincy Jones, has expressed her grief and love for her father following his recent passing. In a heartfelt message, she recalled the special "Jazz Hours" he shared with her, calling it an honor to be his daughter and expressing that his love will endure. Quincy Jones himself had acknowledged his daughter's impact in his final Instagram post, acknowledging his seven children, including Rashida. Despite their father's absence, Rashida has formed strong bonds with her siblings, and her family's creative legacy has contributed to her own success, resulting in an estimated net worth of $25 million. Close to her father, Jones protected her fiercely, and she honored him as a man who embodied love.
